ygData.messageBody:
Wow, I just thought up a new EQ scheme. I'm gonna be an EQ counselor :-)
Start charging wonderful high level bard items for listening to people's
fears of spiders, leeches, their eq love life trials and guild disputes
!!!!! I could be RICH!

-----Original Message-----
From: Kimes, Dean W. [mailto:dean_kimes@...]
Sent: Wednesday, May 17, 2000 11:11 AM
To: 'eqbards@egroups.com'
Subject: RE: [eqbards] kunark level 21

I just close my eyes and navigate by stream sounds ;-)
Those half-spiders
ick me out something fierce.

Kitasi

-----Original Message-----
From: Cranfill, Wendy [mailto:Wendy_Cranfill@...]
Sent: Wednesday, May 17, 2000 11:11 AM
To: 'eqbards@egroups.com'
Subject: RE: [eqbards] kunark level 21


I was running Hally to Karnors this morning from FV and at
one point, I was
SURROUNDED by those spiders. I was sooooo queezed out.
OMG. I mean I was
seriously almost shaking. Do they have counseling for this
kind of stuff? I
think I'm scarred for life.

Ok, I promise I'll stop obsessing about the spiders now...

From: Perhaps a Princess...
[mailto:sarah@...]
Sent: Wednesday, May 17, 2000 11:09 AM
To: eqbards@egroups.com
Subject: RE: [eqbards] kunark level
21

Lake of Ill Omen.

I went to Kunark at level 19 and have worked
my way up to
Level 26, mostly
in the Lake, but also in Warsliks Wood,
fighting Forest
Giants.
I am ready now to go to Frontier Mountains.

The hardest part of Kunark is getting
through Firiona Vie
without
being slaughtered by the spiders.

If you can, get someone to invis you. SOme
see thorugh
invisibile,
but most don't.
